        <title type="html"><![CDATA[WTTP Across Chains: The Multi-Network Web]]></title>
        <id>https://docs.thedip.net/blog/wttp-across-chains</id>
        <link href="https://docs.thedip.net/blog/wttp-across-chains"/>
        <updated>2024-12-06T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[The web doesn’t stop at one server.]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The web doesn’t stop at one server.<br>
<!-- -->So why should the decentralized web stop at one chain?</p>
<p>WTTP was designed for <strong>multi-network support</strong> from day one.</p>
<!-- -->
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="-what-multi-network-means">🌐 What Multi-Network Means<a href="https://docs.thedip.net/blog/wttp-across-chains#-what-multi-network-means" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🌐 What Multi-Network Means" title="Direct link to 🌐 What Multi-Network Means">​</a></h2>
<p>WTTP sites can be deployed on:</p>
<ul>
<li>Ethereum</li>
<li>Polygon</li>
<li>Base</li>
<li>Arbitrum</li>
<li>Fantom</li>
<li>Avalanche<br>
<!-- -->…and more.</li>
</ul>
<p>Each network is just another home for your site.</p>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="-benefits">⚡ Benefits<a href="https://docs.thedip.net/blog/wttp-across-chains#-benefits" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to ⚡ Benefits" title="Direct link to ⚡ Benefits">​</a></h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Resilience</strong><br>
<!-- -->If one chain slows down, your site still lives elsewhere.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Choice</strong><br>
<!-- -->Developers can pick the network that best fits their needs (fees, speed, community).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Interoperability</strong><br>
<!-- -->A WTTP link doesn’t care which chain it’s on—the protocol handles the rest.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="-under-the-hood">🔧 Under the Hood<a href="https://docs.thedip.net/blog/wttp-across-chains#-under-the-hood" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to 🔧 Under the Hood" title="Direct link to 🔧 Under the Hood">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li>The <strong>ProviderManager</strong> handles network switching.</li>
<li>The <strong>ContractManager</strong> keeps track of addresses across chains.</li>
<li>Your <code>wttp.config.json</code> file is the map that ties it all together.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<div class="alert alert--info" role="alert"><div><p>The web was always bigger than one machine.<br>
<!-- -->Now it’s bigger than one blockchain.</p></div></div>]]></content>
